bio.content: Sukshinder Shinda aka The Music Man is a Singer, Director, Producer from Handsworth, Birmingham, UK. He has over 200 album credits to his name. Although he came on the silver screen in 2003 only but he has been serving the Punjabi Music Industry for more than 20 years. The persons behind Shinda's success are his tutors Kuldip Singh Matharu, Laal Singh Bhatti and 'Guru' Ustad Ajit Singh. Although he only entered the singing field(solo albums) in 2003 with Gal Sun Ja(Music Label:Tips,India) he has created a sensation among the Punjabi Music Lovers. In 2005, his latest album BALLE was released with Speed Records,India. The title song BALLE itself involves fusion of different beats adding to the beauty of the song. Most of Shinda's Videos are directed by Baljit Singh Deol and are mostly shot in foreign locations. Shinda, also known for displaying swanky cars in his videos has just released new video PUNJABI CLAP featuring Takeova ENT. The video itself tells the qualities of the man behind it that is Baljit Singh. Shinda helped Jaswinder Singh Bains aka Jazzy B launch his career in 1994 by producing and composing his first album Ghugian da Johra. Since then, Jazzy B became a hit. Any album with the name Sukshinder Shinda associated with it is ought to be a hit. Take example of Amrinder Gill's Dildarian. During the pre-release period promos were aired featuring names of Shinda and Baljit Singh Deol and with good guitar music. Due to this the Punjabi music lovers were eagerly waiting for the release of Gill's album and after release he also became a star. Hes a legend. Sukhshinder Shinda Collaborations Shinda has finished working with various artists including Jazzy B, and legendary's such as Gurdas Maan and Abrar-Ul-haq. He has Released his next Album entitiled as Sukhshinder Shinda Collaborations. Released on 30th June 2006. Read more on Last.fm.
